# Code owners for the assurance layer.
#
# Copy this file to .github/CODEOWNERS in the adopting repository (merge the
# entries into an existing CODEOWNERS if one exists) and replace the
# placeholder with the human owner's @handle or @org/team.
#
# Purpose: changes to the assurance artifacts must pass the human owner, so
# an agent cannot silently weaken an invariant, close a residual, or move
# the upstream pin (PROFILE.md sections 3 and 15). File ownership alone
# enforces nothing: enable branch protection with required reviews and
# "Require review from Code Owners" on the default branch. In a
# single-maintainer repository GitHub does not allow self-approval, so the
# binding becomes fully effective only once a second maintainer exists —
# until then it is a declared intention, and the review record remains the
# effective control.

AGENTS.md                         @REPLACE_WITH_OWNER_OR_TEAM
AGENTIC_ASSURANCE.md              @REPLACE_WITH_OWNER_OR_TEAM
/.agentic-assurance/              @REPLACE_WITH_OWNER_OR_TEAM
/assurance/                       @REPLACE_WITH_OWNER_OR_TEAM
/.github/workflows/assurance.yml  @REPLACE_WITH_OWNER_OR_TEAM
/.github/CODEOWNERS               @REPLACE_WITH_OWNER_OR_TEAM
